        <body>
            <msDesc>
                <msIdentifier>
                    <msName xml:lang="en" type="general">lectionary gospel</msName>
                    <country>Sweden</country>
                    <settlement>Stockholm</settlement>
                    <repository>Royal Library</repository>
                    <idno type="shelfmark">A787a15</idno>
                    <note>The fragment is a part from the 15th-century Russian Evangelion Aprakos
                        (Codex F, ff. 2-3 in <ref type="bibl" target="bib:Wesslén1985">Wessél
                            1985</ref>), represented by a few more leaves, kept in various
                        collections (<ref type="bibl" target="bib:Steensland2005">Steensland
                            2005</ref>): 1. National Record Office, Stockholm, Stafs. IV: 10 (Fr
                        11391); RA, Fr 11521 (codex 1658). 2. Royal Library, Stockholm A787a15:A-B;
                        3. Biblioteka Adademii nauk, Sankt-Petersburg 4.9.7: 2-3, 5; 6-8; 4. Royal
                        Library, Stockholm A787a10:A-B, C-D; 5. Royal Library, Stockholm A787a6; 6.
                        The British Library, Add. 34386, f.29; 7. Royal Library, Stockholm
                        A787a23;</note>
                </msIdentifier>
                <physDesc>
                    <objectDesc form="fragment">
                        <supportDesc material="parch">
                            <support>
                                <material>Parchment of very fine quality. The recto is the hair
                                    side, the verso is the slesh side, respectively.</material>
                            </support>
                            <extent>
                                <measure unit="folia">2 (bifolium)</measure>
                                <dimensions unit="mm" type="folia">
                                    <height>ca232</height>
                                    <width>ca165</width>
                                </dimensions>
                            </extent>
                            <condition>It is a 2-leaf fragment (bifolium) that had been considerably
                                cut down all around. The upper part of the both leaves is missing.
                                F. 2 is in additional cut diagonally toward the lower outer corner.
                                The uppermost line, the last letters in lines 1a: 2-10, 12 and the
                                first letters in line 1b:2-9 are missing. Some letters in the
                                uppermost line of f.2 are also gone. There are some tears and holes
                                from binding.</condition>
                        </supportDesc>
                        <layoutDesc>
                            <layout columns="1" writtenLines="18" ruledLines="18"/>
                        </layoutDesc>
                    </objectDesc>
                    <ink xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0">Brownish for the main
                        text, red and gold for the titles and the initials.</ink>
                    <decoDesc>
                        <p>Intials <foreign xml:lang="cu">Р</foreign> on f. 1r and f. 2v ca 40 mm (4
                            lines) of heigh, being half outside the text column. The initials are
                            red covered with gold. The same technique is applied to the rubrics
                            (titles) introducing the readings (ff. 1r, 1v, 2v).</p>
                    </decoDesc>
                    <bindingDesc>
                        <binding>
                            <summary>Kept together with other parchment fragments (A787a)</summary>
                        </binding>
                    </bindingDesc>
                    <additions type="inscriptions">
                        <list><item><locus>1r</locus><note>A circled figure 15 in pencil</note></item></list>
                    </additions>
                </physDesc>
                <scribeDesc xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0">
                    <scribe n="1">
                        <locus xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">1r-2v</locus>
                        <name xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" role="scribe">anonymous</name>
                        <scriptDesc xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
                            <scriptNote script="Cyrs" style="uncial"><dimensions type="chars" unit="mm"><height>5</height></dimensions>; <dimensions type="line-spacing" unit="mm"><height>12</height></dimensions></scriptNote>
                        </scriptDesc>
                        <scribeLang>
                            <summary xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Russian, Church Slavonic</summary>
                        </scribeLang>
                    </scribe>
                </scribeDesc>
                <msContents>
                    <summary>The fragment contains Matthew 21.27–33, 43–46, and Matthew 27.16–23,
                        23.13–14 with some lacunae</summary>
                    <filiation type="protograph">Russian</filiation>
                    <msItemStruct xml:id="ACD1">
                        <locus n="1">1r–2v</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="bg">Изборно евангелие</title>
                        <filiation type="antigraph">Russian</filiation>
                        <sampleText xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0" xml:lang="cu">
                            <ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="f.1r">сїа творю: ср
                                    <unclear>....</unclear></ab>
                            <ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="f.1v">понеже ꙗко пр<seg rend="sup">о҃</seg>рка оучн҃комъ</ab>
                            <ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="2r">гошѧ его исцѣ
                                    <unclear>....</unclear></ab>
                            <ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="2v">вы бо не въсходи</ab>
                        </sampleText>
                    </msItemStruct>
                </msContents>
